ematicians experience. Walker draws upon these narratives to suggest ways to capitalize on the power and potential of underserved communities to respond to the national imperative for developing math success for new generations of young people.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aAfrican American mathematiciansxEducation (Graduate). 0aAfrican American mathematicians. 0aDoctor of philosophy degreexUnited States. 4aAfrican American Studies : African American Studies. 4aEducation : Education. 4aEducation : Higher Education. 4aEducation : Teacher Education. 4aScience, Mathematics, and Technology : Mathematics. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / African American Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2014z978311149015140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438452173423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438452173/original  a978-3-11-149015-1  SUNY Press eBook Package 2014b2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles